text.tspan: Fertility rate vs. GDP per capita, 2019
The fertility rate, expressed as the number of children per woman, is based on age-specific fertility rates in one
particular year. This is shown against gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, adjusted for differences in the
cost of living between countries, and for inflation.
Births per woman (live births per woman)
Data source: UN, World Population Prospects (2024); Feenstra et al. (2015), Penn World Table (2021)
